# Development Workflow & Best Practices

## Getting Started

1. Install dependencies: `pnpm install`
2. Set up environment variables in `.env`
3. Initialize database: `pnpm db:push`
4. Start development: `pnpm dev`

## Code Quality

- Run type checking: `pnpm typecheck`
- Run linting: `pnpm lint` or `pnpm lint:fix`
- Format code: `pnpm format:write`
- Full check: `pnpm check` (combines lint + typecheck)

## Database Workflow

- Schema changes: Edit [prisma/schema.prisma](mdc:prisma/schema.prisma) â†’ `pnpm db:push`
- View data: `pnpm db:studio`
- Reset database: `pnpm db:push --force-reset` (development only)

## API Development

1. Define Zod schema for input validation
2. Create procedure in appropriate router file
3. Test with tRPC client in components
4. Use TypeScript types from tRPC for type safety

## Component Development

1. Start with Server Component when possible
2. Add `"use client"` only when interactivity needed
3. Use tRPC hooks for data fetching
4. Style with Tailwind utilities
5. Test component behavior in browser

## Environment Configuration

- Development: Uses `.env` file
- Database: PostgreSQL (configured in `DATABASE_URL`)
- Hot reload enabled with Turbo mode
- Prisma generates types on `postinstall`

## Production Deployment

- Build: `pnpm build`
- Database migrations: `pnpm db:migrate`
- Type safety verified at build time
- Environment variables must be set in production
